question: Please provide names of the patients that are linked with the organization ROYAL OF FAIRHAVEN NURSING CENTER.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT DISTINCT ?first ?last WHERE { ?organization a syn:Organization; syn:id ?organizationId; syn:name 'ROYAL OF FAIRHAVEN NURSING CENTER'^^pl:. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:organizationId ?organizationId; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientId; syn:first ?first; syn:last ?last. }
sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.first, p.last FROM organizations org LEFT JOIN encounters e ON org.id=e.organization LEFT JOIN patients p ON e.patient=p.id WHERE org.name='ROYAL OF FAIRHAVEN NURSING CENTER';
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'ROYAL OF FAIRHAVEN NURSING CENTER'})-[:IS_PERFOMED_AT]->(e:Encounter)<-[:HAS_ENCOUNTER]-(p:Patient) RETURN DISTINCT p.firstName, p.lastName
mql: db.organizations.aggregate([    { $match: { "NAME": "ROYAL OF FAIRHAVEN NURSING CENTER" } },    { $lookup: {        from: "patients",        localField: "ORGANIZATION_ID",        foreignField: "ENCOUNTERS.ORGANIZATION_REF",        as: "op"    }},    { $unwind: "$op" },    { $unwind: "$op.ENCOUNTERS"},    { $match: { "NAME": "ROYAL OF FAIRHAVEN NURSING CENTER" } },    { $group: {_id: {first: "$op.FIRST", last: "$op.LAST"}} },    { $project: {_id: 0, first: "$_id.first", last: "$_id.last" } }])

question: Please provide me the provider associated with the claim of ID d3f2128e-ce69-2537-a97e-546e63c256e5.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  DISTINCT ?name WHERE {  ?claim a syn:Claim;syn:id 'd3f2128e-ce69-2537-a97e-546e63c256e5'^^uuid:; syn:providerId ?providerId. ?provider a syn:Provider; syn:id ?providerId; syn:name ?name.}

mql:
db.patients.aggregate([
    {$match: {"CLAIMS.CLAIM_ID": "d3f2128e-ce69-2537-a97e-546e63c256e5"}},
    {$unwind: "$CLAIMS"},
    {$lookup: {
               from: "providers",
               localField: "CLAIMS.CLAIM_TRANSACTIONS.PROVIDER_REF",
               foreignField: "PROVIDER_ID",
               as: "_provider"}},
     {$unwind: "$CLAIMS"},
     {$unwind: "$CLAIMS.CLAIM_TRANSACTIONS"},
     {$unwind: "$_provider" },
     {$match: {"CLAIMS.CLAIM_ID": "d3f2128e-ce69-2537-a97e-546e63c256e5" } },    
     {$group: {_id: {provider_name: "$_provider.NAME"} } },    
     {$project: {_id: 0, NAME: "$_id.provider_name" } },]);

sql: SELECT DISTINCT e.description FROM organizations org LEFT JOIN encounters e ON e.organization=org.id WHERE org.name='WOONSOCKET URGENT CARE PC';
cypher: MATCH (e:Encounter)-[:IS_RESPONSIBLE_FOR]->(o:Organization {name: 'WOONSOCKET URGENT CARE PC'}) RETURN DISTINCT e.description;

question: What encounter is associated with the organization BRIGHTON HOUSE REHABILITATION & NURSING CENTER?

sql: SELECT DISTINCT e.description FROM organizations org LEFT JOIN encounters e ON e.organization=org.id WHERE org.name='BRIGHTON HOUSE REHABILITATION & NURSING CENTER';

question: Which payer paid for the medication Warfarin Sodium 5 MG Oral Tablet?

mql: db.organizations.aggregate([    { $match: { "NAME": "HOSPICE SERVICES OF WESTERN & CENTRAL MASS" } },    { $lookup: {        from: "patients",        localField: "ORGANIZATION_ID",        foreignField: "ENCOUNTERS.ORGANIZATION_REF",        as: "op"    }},    { $unwind: "$op" },    { $unwind: "$op.ENCOUNTERS"},    { $match: { "NAME": "HOSPICE SERVICES OF WESTERN & CENTRAL MASS" } },    { $group: {_id: "$op.ENCOUNTERS.DESCRIPTION" } },    { $project: {_id: 0, encounter_description: "$_id" } }])

question: What is the start date of the procedure Assessment of substance use (procedure)?

sql: SELECT start FROM procedures WHERE description='Assessment of substance use (procedure)';
cypher: MATCH (p:Procedure {description: 'Assessment of substance use (procedure)'}) RETURN p.start;
mql: db.patients.aggregate(    [{        $match: {"ENCOUNTERS.PROCEDURES.DESCRIPTION": "Assessment of substance use (procedure)"}    },    {        $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS"    },    {        $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS.PROCEDURES"    },    {        $match: {"ENCOUNTERS.PROCEDURES.DESCRIPTION": "Assessment of substance use (procedure)"}    },    {        $group: {            _id: "$ENCOUNTERS.PROCEDURES.START"        }    },    {        $project: {            _id: 0,            start: "$_id"        }    },    ]    )

cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'EASTERN & WESTERN MEDICAL CENTER PC'})-[:IS_PERFOMED_AT]->(e:Encounter)<-[:HAS_ENCOUNTER]-(p:Patient) RETURN DISTINCT p.firstName, p.lastName
mql: db.organizations.aggregate([    { $match: { "NAME": "EASTERN & WESTERN MEDICAL CENTER PC" } },    { $lookup: {        from: "patients",        localField: "ORGANIZATION_ID",        foreignField: "ENCOUNTERS.ORGANIZATION_REF",        as: "op"    }},    { $unwind: "$op" },    { $group: {_id: { first: "$op.FIRST", last: "$op.LAST" } } },    { $project: {_id: 0, FIRST: "$_id.first", LAST: "$_id.last" } }])

question: Who is associated with the organization LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT DISTINCT ?first ?last WHERE { ?organization a syn:Organization; syn:id ?organizationId; syn:name 'LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM'^^pl:. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:organizationId ?organizationId; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientId; syn:first ?first; syn:last ?last. }
sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.first, p.last FROM organizations org LEFT JOIN encounters e ON org.id=e.organization LEFT JOIN patients p ON e.patient=p.id WHERE org.name='LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM';
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM'})-[:IS_PERFOMED_AT]->(e:Encounter)<-[:HAS_ENCOUNTER]-(p:Patient) RETURN DISTINCT p.firstName, p.lastName
mql: db.organizations.aggregate([    { $match: { "NAME": "LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM" } },    { $lookup: {        from: "patients",        localField: "ORGANIZATION_ID",        foreignField: "ENCOUNTERS.ORGANIZATION_REF",        as: "op"    }},    { $unwind: "$op" },    { $group: {_id: { first: "$op.FIRST", last: "$op.LAST" } } },    { $project: {_id: 0, FIRST: "$_id.first", LAST: "$_id.last" } }])

question: Please provide me the patients associated with the supply named Blood glucose testing strips (physical object).

sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.first, p.last FROM supplies s LEFT JOIN patients p ON s.patient=p.id WHERE s.description='Blood glucose testing strips (physical object)';

mql: db.patients.aggregate([    {        $match: {"ENCOUNTERS.SUPPLIES.DESCRIPTION": 'Blood glucose testing strips (physical object)'}    },    {        $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS"    },    {        $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS.SUPPLIES"    },    {        $match: {"ENCOUNTERS.SUPPLIES.DESCRIPTION": 'Blood glucose testing strips (physical object)'}    },    {        $group: {            _id: {                FIRST: "$FIRST",                LAST: "$LAST"            }        }    },    {        $project: {            _id: 0,            first: "$_id.FIRST",            last: "$_id.LAST"        }    },])

question: What is the reason for performing the procedure Premature birth of newborn?

question: How many patients have the allergy described as Allergy to substance (finding)?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?patientId) as ?count) WHERE { ?allergy a syn:Allergy ; syn:description 'Allergy to substance (finding)'^^pl:; syn:patientId ?patientId. }
sql: SELECT COUNT(*) as count_allergic_patients FROM allergies a LEFT JOIN patients p ON a.patient = p.id WHERE a.description='Allergy to substance (finding)';
cypher: MATCH (p:Patient)-[:HAS_ALLERGY]->(a:Allergy {description: 'Allergy to substance (finding)'}) RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT p) AS numberOfPatients;
mql: db.patients.aggregate([  { $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS" },  { $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS.ALLERGIES" },  { $match: { "ENCOUNTERS.ALLERGIES.DESCRIPTION": "Allergy to substance (finding)" } },  { $group: { _id: null, count: { $sum: 1 } } },  { $project: { _id: 0, count: 1 } }])

sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.first, p.last FROM observations ob LEFT JOIN patients p ON ob.patient=p.id WHERE ob.description='Respiratory rate';
cypher: MATCH (p:Patient)-[:HAS_HISTORY_OF]->(o:Observation {description: 'Respiratory rate'}) RETURN DISTINCT p.firstName, p.lastName;
mql: db.patients.aggregate([    { $match: {"ENCOUNTERS.OBSERVATIONS.DESCRIPTION": "Respiratory rate"} },    { $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS" },    { $unwind: "$ENCOUNTERS.OBSERVATIONS" },    { $match: { "ENCOUNTERS.OBSERVATIONS.DESCRIPTION": "Respiratory rate"} },    { $group: { _id: { first: "$FIRST", last: "$LAST" } } },    { $project: { _id: 0, FIRST: "$_id.first", LAST: "$_id.last" } }])

question: Please provide names of the patients that are linked with the organization SECURE HOME HEALTH CARE INCORPORATED.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT DISTINCT ?first ?last WHERE { ?organization a syn:Organization; syn:id ?organizationId; syn:name 'SECURE HOME HEALTH CARE INCORPORATED'^^pl:. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:organizationId ?organizationId; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientId; syn:first ?first; syn:last ?last. }
sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.first, p.last FROM organizations org LEFT JOIN encounters e ON org.id=e.organization LEFT JOIN patients p ON e.patient=p.id WHERE org.name='SECURE HOME HEALTH CARE INCORPORATED';
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'SECURE HOME HEALTH CARE INCORPORATED'})-[:IS_PERFOMED_AT]->(e:Encounter)<-[:HAS_ENCOUNTER]-(p:Patient) RETURN DISTINCT p.firstName, p.lastName
mql: db.organizations.aggregate([    { $match: { "NAME": "SECURE HOME HEALTH CARE INCORPORATED" } },    { $lookup: {        from: "patients",        localField: "ORGANIZATION_ID",        foreignField: "ENCOUNTERS.ORGANIZATION_REF",        as: "op"    }},    { $unwind: "$op" },    { $unwind: "$op.ENCOUNTERS"},    { $match: { "NAME": "SECURE HOME HEALTH CARE INCORPORATED" } },    { $group: {_id: {first: "$op.FIRST", last: "$op.LAST"}} },    { $project: {_id: 0, first: "$_id.first", last: "$_id.last" } }])

sql: SELECT DISTINCT e.description FROM organizations org LEFT JOIN encounters e ON e.organization=org.id WHERE org.name='HOLYOKE MEDICAL CENTER INC';
cypher: MATCH (e:Encounter)-[:IS_RESPONSIBLE_FOR]->(o:Organization {name: 'HOLYOKE MEDICAL CENTER INC'}) RETURN DISTINCT e.description;
mql: db.organizations.aggregate([    { $match: { "NAME": "HOLYOKE MEDICAL CENTER INC" } },    { $lookup: {        from: "patients",        localField: "ORGANIZATION_ID",        foreignField: "ENCOUNTERS.ORGANIZATION_REF",        as: "op"    }},    { $unwind: "$op" },    { $unwind: "$op.ENCOUNTERS"},    { $match: { "NAME": "HOLYOKE MEDICAL CENTER INC" } },    { $group: {_id: "$op.ENCOUNTERS.DESCRIPTION" } },    { $project: {_id: 0, encounter_description: "$_id" } }])

question: Please provide the list of patients associated with the payer NO_INSURANCE.

sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.first, p.last FROM payers py LEFT JOIN payer_transitions pt ON py.id=pt.payer LEFT JOIN patients p ON pt.patient=p.id WHERE py.name='NO_INSURANCE';

sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.first, p.last FROM patients p LEFT JOIN careplans c ON c.patient=p.id WHERE c.code='736690008';
